cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with learning graph embeddings for semantic similarity and word sense disambiguation tasks, which are typically studied in the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new approach for learning embeddings that relies on structural measures of node similarities, which is a machine learning problem and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses WordNet as the source of gold similarities, which is a knowledge representation and reasoning task and can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed model is computationally efficient, which is a relevant aspect of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) categories.
